Check Point Balance API Overview


• Endpoint URL: `/payment-option`
• HTTP Method: `POST`
• Authentication: Bearer Token

Request Example


Here’s how you can make a request to check the point balance:

bash
Copy
curl -X POST \
  https://pluraluat.v2.pinepg.in/payment-option \
  -H 'Content-Type: application/json' \
  -H 'Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN' \
  -d '{
    "payment_option": {
      "points_card_details": {
        "card_last4": "1112",
        "card_number": "4012001037141112",
        "registered_mobile_number": "7827709063"
      }
    },
    "order_details": {
      "order_amount": {
        "value": 5000,
        "currency": "INR"
      }
    }
  }'



Request Parameters


• payment_option: Contains details about the points card.
• points_card_details:
• `card_last4` (string): Last four digits of the card.
• `card_number` (string): Full card number.
• `registered_mobile_number` (string): Mobile number registered with the card.
• order_details: Contains details about the order.
• order_amount:
• `value` (integer): Amount for the order.
• `currency` (string): Currency type (e.g., "INR").

Sample Response


A successful response will look like this:

json
Copy
{
  "balance": {
    "value": 23718050,
    "currency": "INR"
  },
  "redeemable_amount": {
    "value": 3500,
    "currency": "INR"
  },
  "redeemable_points": 140,
  "is_eligible": true
}



Response Parameters


• balance:
• `value` (integer): Total balance available on the card.
• `currency` (string): Currency type.
• redeemable_amount:
• `value` (integer): Amount that can be redeemed.
• `currency` (string): Currency type.
• redeemable_points (integer): Total redeemable points available on the card.
• is_eligible (boolean): Indicates if the card is eligible for redemption.

Error Handling


Make sure to handle potential errors, such as:

• 400 Bad Request: Invalid input parameters.
• 401 Unauthorized: Invalid or missing authentication token.
• 422 Unprocessable Entity: Validation errors.
• 500 Internal Server Error: Server-side issues.

Security Considerations


• Always use HTTPS for API calls to ensure data security.
• Store your API tokens securely and do not expose them in your code.

